cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.GR 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for tracking multiple people in complex group activities from multiple handheld cameras. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves multitask learning, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of physical human constraints and 3D skeleton reconstruction suggests the involvement of robotics, which falls under cs.RO (Robotics and Control). The paper also involves clustering and association, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with group activities, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics).
